<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-150-034 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 761 602</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  May 22 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Palm-top computer with optical data transfer system. (Sony Corp.'sPTC-300 portable microcomputer) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miyazawa, Masayuki.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sony Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Sony PTC-300 (Portable computer) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionHand-held computersOptical communicationsInfrared technologyHandwritingI/O Devices.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>PALM-TOP COMPUTER WITH OPTICAL DATA TRANSFER SYSTEM 05/22/91 TOKYO, JAPAN,1991 MAY 22 (NB) -- Sony has upgraded its palm-top computer to include ahandwriting input system.andP;  The &quot;PTC-300&quot; weighs only 355 grams and measures16.5 x 15 x 2.8cm -- roughly half the size of its predecessor.andP;  It's alsocheaper -- 65,000 yen ($480), while the earlier version cost 165,000 yen($1,200).andM;The PTC-300 employs fuzzy theory for handwriting input.andP;  This enables thedevice to translate 3,553 kinds of handwritten letters, the company says,including Kanji.andM;Sony's palm-top computer is based around Motorola's 68000 chip.andP;  It has a3.4-inch, high resolution liquid crystal display with 256 x 320 pixels.andM;One unique aspect of this palm-top computer is that it can exchange data withother devices via an infrared beam; it has a built-in optical telecominterface and requires no cable.andM;This PC also has a built-in RS-232C port for exchanging data with desktoppersonal computers.andP;  A thermal printer is sold at 35,000 yen ($260).andM;(Masayuki Miyazawa/19910522/Press Contact: Sony, andplus;81-3-3448-2200 Fax,andplus;81-3-3448-3061)</TEXT></DOC>